## Findings Presentation Standard

When presenting findings that classify items into categories (e.g.,
"6 safe, 4 need verification, 2 not removable"), never present just
the summary counts. Every finding must be immediately actionable
without follow-up questions. For each category:

1. **Explain WHY** items are in this category — the classification
   criterion, not just the label
2. **List each item** with its specific reasoning (use tables for
   3+ items)
3. **State the concrete consequence** of acting or not acting on each
   item — what breaks, what changes, what happens
4. **Give the specific next action** — not "verify this" but exactly
   what to verify, how, and who should do it

The test: could someone act on this finding without asking a single
follow-up question? If not, the finding is incomplete.

## Exhaust Your Own Capabilities First

Before proposing that a human verifies something, delivers something,
or decides something — check whether you can resolve it yourself using
the tools and sources available to you. This applies to every kind of
output: open questions, action items, dependencies, recommendations.

Only create work for humans when you have confirmed the information or
decision genuinely cannot be derived from your available sources.

## External Systems — Read Only by Default

No agent may write to any external system without explicit user approval.
This includes: Jira comments, issue updates, status transitions, Confluence
edits, Slack messages, git pushes, deployments, and any other action that
modifies state outside the local project. Reading is always fine.

## Pipeline Order Reference

```
NEW PROJECT
install -> CLAUDE.md -> [DR]/[TR] -> [DP] -> [SI] -> Party Mode
-> SF Adversarial Review -> [CV] Claim Verification
-> [IV] Independent Verification (if client-facing) -> Advanced Elicitation -> Build

EXISTING PROJECT - NEW TASK
Update CLAUDE.md -> [SI] (fresh for this ticket) -> Party Mode
-> SF Adversarial Review -> [CV] Claim Verification
-> [IV] Independent Verification (if client-facing) -> Advanced Elicitation -> Build

EXISTING PROJECT - CONTINUING SAME TASK
Check INVESTIGATION.md currency -> update if needed
-> Party Mode -> SF Adversarial Review -> [CV] -> [IV] if client-facing -> continue Build

QUICK TASK (bug fix, config change, small story)
[SI] (scoped tight) -> Party Mode -> SF Adversarial Review -> [CV] -> Build
```

